\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. diae} (Rech. fil.) Meusel & Kästner, {\i Feddes Repert.} {\b 83}: 228 (1972) ({\i Lyrolepis diae} Rech. fil.). Plant densely white-tomentose throughout. Flowering stems 40-60 cm, erect, sparsely leafy. Leaves mostly crowded on short non-flowering branches, oblanceolate, obtuse to acute, entire. Capitula 15-20 mm in diameter, in small corymbs of 2-4. Outer involucral bracts 10-15 × 3-5 mm, entire or pinnatifid; inner bracts 10-16 mm. Florets yellow.{\i  Calcareous maritime cliffs. • Small islands off the N. coast of Kriti.} Cr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. tragacanthifolia} Klatt, {\i Leopoldina}{\b  20}: 94 (1884) ({\i Atractylis conformis} W. Barbey & Major). Plant white-tomentose throughout. Stems 15-20 cm, branched from the base, forming a fairly dense cushion. Leaves dimorphic, the earliest of each year's growth oblanceolate, entire or somewhat pinnatifid, soft, without spines, the remainder c. 5 cm, narrowly linear, coriaceous, canaliculate, with a terminal spine and 2-3 lateral spines 12-15 mm on each side. Capitula 8-20 mm in diameter, terminal. Outer involucral bracts 20-50 mm, similar to the upper leaves; inner bracts c. 10 mm. Florets pale yellow.{\i  Karpathos.} Cr. ({\i Rhodos}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Subgen. {\b Carlina}. Annual to perennial, monocarpic or with subterranean stock. All leaves spiny. Inner involucral bracts variously coloured.
