\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. C. corymbosa} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 828, [1231] (1753). Subglabrous to sparsely arachnoid-tomentose perennial (10-)20-50(-80) cm, with one or more stems arising from an underground rhizome. Leaves up to 9 × 3 cm, oblong-lanceolate to ovate, dentate to pinnatisect, undulate, with strongly spinose margin. Capitula 12-20 mm in diameter, solitary on short branches, forming a rather dense corymb. Inner involucral bracts 10-16 × 1·5-2·5 mm, bright or brownish yellow. Florets yellow. Achenes c. 2·5 mm; pappus c. 8 mm. 2n = 18, 20. {\i S. Europe.} Al Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par

\par

