\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. C. sicula} Ten., {\i Cat. Pl. Horti Neap., App.} ed. 2, 74 (1819). Subglabrous perennial; stem 20-70 cm, simple or with very short branches. Leaves c. 7 × 2 cm, oblong, pinnatisect, spiny. Capitula 25-35 mm in diameter, in a crowded terminal cluster of 2-4; sometimes 1-2 capitula subsessile in leaf-axils lower down. Outer involucral bracts up to 45 mm, exceeding the inner; inner bracts 12-15 × 2·5-3 mm, silvery-white above, white or purplish beneath. Florets yellow. Achenes c. 3 mm; pappus c. 9 mm.{\i  S.E. Italy, Sicilia and smaller islands of C. Mediterranean region.} It Si.
